Sentencas: High-entropy perovskite cathode materials with the coupling of five or more different component transition metal species can provide great flexibility in modulating the electronic properties and catalytic activities for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: New approach to enhance Sr-free cathode performance by high-entropy multi-component transition metal coupling

Sentencas: Herein, as-prepared Sr-free high-entropy perovskite oxide LaMnO3-delta (LMO) is homogeneously incorporated five transition metal species Mn, Fe, Co, Ni and Cu (LaMn0.2Fe0.2Co0.2Ni0.2Cu0.2O3-delta, HELMO) in B-site of perovskite, presenting enhanced electrochemical performance.
Titulo: New approach to enhance Sr-free cathode performance by high-entropy multi-component transition metal coupling

Sentencas: The cell performance of anode supported SOFCs with HE-LMO cathode is almost one point five times (550.89 mW cm-2 at 800 C) of those with LMO cathode.
Titulo: New approach to enhance Sr-free cathode performance by high-entropy multi-component transition metal coupling

Sentencas: Accordingly, the electrode polarization resistances of HE-LMO cathode are reduced from 0.532 omega cm2 to 0.212 omega cm2 at 800 C and from 4.051 omega cm2 to 1.538 omega cm2 at 650 C, respectively.
Titulo: New approach to enhance Sr-free cathode performance by high-entropy multi-component transition metal coupling

Sentencas: All the results demonstrate that it would be a feasible way to design high-performance cathode materials with multi-component transition metal coupling at reduced temperature.
Titulo: New approach to enhance Sr-free cathode performance by high-entropy multi-component transition metal coupling
